This directory contains several examples that exercise different features of
Qu-Prolog.

Examples featuring the extended data structures:

lambda.ql, lambda2.ql, lambda_type.ql - 
     lambda term processors.
natural_deduction.ql -  
     a simple interactive prover.
incomplete_unify.ql -
     a heuristic unifier for finding unifiers of delayed unification problems.

Examples featuring communication and threads:

http_connect.ql -
	An example using TCP/IP
tcp_server.ql, tcp_client.ql - 
	A simple TCP/IP server/client example
linda_server.ql, linda_client.ql -
    A multi-threaded implementaion of the Linda model 
db.ql -
	a simple database server
producer.ql, consumer.ql -
	A simple producer-consumer example using Elvin communication
router_monitor.ql -
	A simple monitor for ICM messages

Examples of using the ICM extensions to Tcl/Tk
monitor_gui -
	A GUI version of router_monitor.ql
template_gui -
	A template GUI to aid in the construction of a Tcl/Tk GUI that uses
	ICM communication.
cc_icm -
	A directory containing definitions of an ICM communications class, a class
	for encoding and decoding compressed Qu-Prolog terms, and a simple example
	using both.

Examples of using QT
../src/xqp -
	A directory containing the source code for the xqp interface. It uses pipes
	to connect stdio of a process (typically a Qu-Prolog process) to a QP 
	widget.
../src/xqpdebug -
	A directory containing the source code for the xqpdebug interface.
	It uses ICM communication to connect a thread of a Qu-Prolog process to
	a QP widget.

